title: find and findLast return undefined on failure
body:
TypeScript now has a strict null checking option. When it is turned on, types that can be `undefined` or `null` must explicitly say so.

This fixes the find/findLast methods so that they declare their potential to return `undefined`.

title: Start on updating Ember to 2.X
body:
The declaration file for Ember is stuck at 1.11.3 and i think a 2.X version is needed. 

So i forked ember.d.ts into 2 files, a version for the major version 1, and another for the major version 2. Following the naming convention that seems to be used in multi-version libraries. 
And then updated the new ember.d.ts file. 

For now it is just updated to 2.0, which was a release [that only removed deprecated features](http://emberjs.com/blog/2015/08/13/ember-2-0-released.html). Which makes updating to it relatively easy.

What i did was to transverse the heap and searched for all properties that had been removed from version 1 to version 2, and then removed those properties, and only those properties. 

I say "only those", since there is a lot of features documented in the declaration file, which do not have a corresponding implementation exported on the heap. As an example, `Ember.Handlebars.print` and `Ember.StateManager` are both undefined in both version 1 and version 2, but i still kept them in the version 2 file, since they didn't change between the versions.

title: Correct param and return types for ShapeUtils triangulation methods.
body:
case 2. Improvement to existing type definition.

The [THREE.ShapeUtils.triangulate](https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L24) function [takes a parameter contour](https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L94) which is an array of THREE.Vector2 which can be seen here: https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L46. 

It returns [either an array of coordinates or indices](https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L185). When coordinates it is an array of arrays of THREE.Vector2 and when indices it is an array of array of number which can be seen here: https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L160.

The [THREE.ShapeUtils.triangulateShape](https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L192) function uses the triangulate function above but always returns the coordinates which can be seen here: https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/blob/master/src/extras/ShapeUtils.js#L642.
